Can this connect to Salesforce or ServiceNow agents?
Yes — any agent with an API endpoint can be registered. SaaS vendor agents like Salesforce AgentForce and ServiceNow are supported through the registry and gateway.
What happens if an agent goes down?
The circuit breaker detects failures and opens automatically, preventing cascading failures. Retry and fallback logic is built in. You can see circuit breaker status live on the Gateway tab.
How is this different from an API Gateway like Apigee?
Apigee manages REST APIs. This manages AI agents specifically — with agent cards, Q-learning policy decisions, token cost tracking, and LLM-specific governance. It's purpose-built for agentic AI.
Can we run this on our own servers?
Yes — this is running on OpenShift on our private cloud right now. It's fully containerised and compatible with any Kubernetes environment. No data leaves your infrastructure.
How do we onboard a new agent?
Fill in the name, owner, framework, and policies in the Register modal. The platform generates the subscription key automatically. Takes under a minute.
Is this GDPR compliant?
Every request is audit-logged. PII masking is a built-in policy. You can configure retention and anonymisation. The Governance tab shows GDPR flags in real time.



